We are currently looking for qualified Osteopaths &amp; Physiotherapists to join our Clinic in Chelsea and Notting Hill.

Join our multidisciplinary team at our bustling Clinic in Chelsea, and soon Notting Hill, London, providing expert bespoke treatments to clients along a team of experienced Physiotherapists, Pilates Instructors and other Health &amp; Fitness Practitioners. All our Practitioners plan and implement therapies to improve patients' condition and/or reduce pain and develop appropriate care plans as well as offer specialist advice and education on how to avoid injury and promote the client‚Äôs future health and wellbeing.

Location: Chelsea &amp; Notting Hill (opening soon)
Job Title: Currently hiring MSK Physiotherapists and Osteopaths
Contract type: Full Time - Permanent
Hours per week: Approx. 40
Salary: Competitive

Benefits:

-Competitive salary;
-Great working environment;
-Comprehensive Training that includes learning techniques used specifically by Club Health and treatment technologies like Laser Therapy;
-Part of a professional team of experts;
-The opportunity to work at a rapidly growing business that can fast-track your career domestically and 

Internationally;

-Have protected CPD time, access to a local in-service training program and training events organised by Club 
-Health Academy including both clinical and leadership courses
-Mentoring support within the department from Clinical Lead and support with career development;
Discounts and access to our Facilities.


Physiotherapist / Osteopath Role and Responsibilities:

-Take professional responsibility as a Chartered Physiotherapist/Osteopath, with high level decision-making, autonomy, and clinical-reasoning skills, to triage, assess, diagnose, and treat a designated clinical caseload;
Comply with all company policies, procedures, guidelines, and regulations, ensuring that product delivery and customer experience is consistent;
-Communicate effectively with clients and/or parents and carers, respecting privacy and confidentiality;
-Communicate effectively with referring parties so that all clients receive continued and uninterrupted care;Consult clients about optimal nutrition, exercise, equipment/devices, sleeping habits, stress management, and other matters that would promote a positive wellbeing and quicker rehabilitation;
-Proactively attract returning and new client business to the clinic site, which should include leading corporate workshops, as prepared by yourself and the partnerships manager, to existing, new and prospective patients;
-Continually strive to improve clinic standards identify any risks to the Clinic Lead and Manager;
Maintain accurate client documentation, records, and statistical information, and complete them in a timely manner and in line with contractual service level agreements;
-Continually develop as a Practitioner and evidence continued professional development (CPD) which should include attending external conferences and events that are beneficial to your own professional development;
-Abide by the CSP's/GOsC‚Äôs Code of Members' Professional Values and Behaviour, and the HCPC‚Äôs Standards of conduct, performance and ethics;
-Support the clinic‚Äôs multidisciplinary team to develop services/products, when required;
-Be flexible with working hours (to include some evening and weekend work).

It‚Äôs equally important that you share our values. We believe in putting people first and providing personalised, comprehensive healthcare. That makes you part of a much wider team, working to create a healthier future for each individual client.


Required Education, Skills and Qualifications:

-BSc Physiotherapy/Osteopathy or equivalent;
-HCPC registration (for Physiotherapists);
-CSP/GOsC registration;
-Previous MSK experience in private practice setting;
-Excellent skills in assessment, diagnosis and treatment of musculoskeletal conditions; 
-Excellent manual therapy skills are essential; 
-Ability to prepare and oversee Rehabilitation Training Plans;
-Excellent command of the English language (both written and spoken);
-Eligibility to work in the UK;
-Appropriate liability insurance and clean DBS.

Apply now: 

Please send your CV and a short covering letter to hello@clubhealth.uk, detailing your Visa situation, if applicable, your current job situation and availability and finally your medium-long term career goals. Please note that for the time being we can only consider candidates that are already eligible to work in the UK.
